{"id":37924,"date":"2022-06-23T14:19:37","date_gmt":"2022-06-23T10:19:37","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=37924"},"modified":"2022-06-23T14:19:37","modified_gmt":"2022-06-23T10:19:37","slug":"respect-father","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/06\/23\/respect-father\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Parents: Respect your father\u2019s loved ones"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Ibn Umar reported: He passed by a bedouin on a journey and the bedouin\u2019s father had been a friend of Umar, may Allah be pleased with him. Ibn Umar said to the bedouin, \u201cAre you not his son?\u201d The bedouin said, \u201cOf course.\u201d Ibn Umar ordered that he be given a donkey from his entourage, and he took off his turban and gave it to him. Those who were with him said, \u201cWould it not have been enough only to give him two coins?\u201d Ibn Umar said, \u201cThe Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said: <strong>Respect the loved ones of your father and do not cut them off, lest Allah extinguish your light.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Adab al-Mufrad 40<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Ibn Hajar<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e \u0645\u064e\u0631\u0651\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064c \u0641\u0650\u064a \u0633\u064e\u0641\u064e\u0631\u064d \u0641\u064e\u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0628\u064f\u0648 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u062f\u0650\u064a\u0642\u064b\u0627 \u0644\u0650\u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0644\u0650\u0644\u0652\u0623